<p>Understanding the capabilities of these APIs will empower you to optimize your integration with Ripple and take full advantage of its benefits.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">API Types and Their Functions in Ripple</h3>



<p>You can explore the key features of Ripple Integration APIs by understanding the various types of APIs and their functions.</p>



<p>The following are the different types of APIs in Ripple and their functions:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>REST API</strong>: This API allows you to access and interact with the Ripple network using HTTP methods. It provides a simple and easy-to-use interface for developers to retrieve account information, send payments, and manage orders.</li>



<li><strong>WebSocket API</strong>: This API enables real-time communication between the client and the Ripple network. It allows you to receive live updates on transactions, order book changes, and other network events.</li>



<li><strong>JSON-RPC API</strong>: This API provides a remote procedure call interface for developers to interact with the Ripple network. It allows you to perform a wide range of operations, such as retrieving account balances, submitting transactions, and managing trust lines.</li>



<li><strong>Transaction Submission API</strong>: This API allows you to submit signed transactions to the Ripple network for processing. It provides a secure and reliable way to broadcast transactions and ensures that they&#8217;re included in the ledger.</li>
</ul>



<p>Understanding the functions of these different types of APIs will help you leverage the connectivity and capabilities of Ripple Integration APIs.</p>



